===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|biscop}}, from {{etyl|VL.}} {{term|biscopus}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|episcopus||overseer, supervisor}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἐπίσκοπος||overseer|tr=episkopos|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|ἐπί||over|tr=epi|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|σκοπέω||I examine|tr=skopeō|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbɪʃəp/}}
* {{audio|En-us-bishop.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{IPA|/ˈbɪʃʃəp/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A high ranking official in the Catholic church who governs a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other denominations and religions. (Occasionally abbreviated as {{term|Bp.|lang=en}} when used as a [[title]].)
# {{chess}} A piece that may be moved only diagonally.
# {{slang}} [[penis]] (see [[bash the bishop]]).
# {{slang}} [[sex toy]].

